    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Foster</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Durham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22,
                            1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 87.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: This Department has been advised by the
                        vice-consul-general of the arrest and confinement at Port au Prince of a
                        respectable American merchant, Mr. Frederick Mevs, under aggravating
                        circumstances.</p>
                <p>It is desired that you will terminate the leave of absence you are now
                        enjoying and return to Port au Prince for the purpose of investigating this
                        affair and taking such action with the Government of Haiti as the
                        circumstances may require.</p>
                <p>The Secretary of the Navy has been requested to transport you to Port au
                        Prince in a vessel of the Navy, and, if public business requires it, to also
                        transport you from Port au Prince to San Domingo City. You will, however,
                        delay the vessel as short a time as possible in this service.</p>
                <p>You are instructed, after ascertaining the real facts of the arrest and
                        confinement of Mr. Mevs, to lay the matter before the Government of Haiti,
                        if the circumstances warrant it, and ask for such action on its part in
                        reparation of this injury to an American citizen as, in your discretion, may
                        seem proper.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John W. Foster.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
